✨ day 44/365 ✨

shared this glam eye look in class today — bold, blended, and full of sparkle! here’s a quick breakdown of the steps:
	1.	apply kajal and blend it on the outer corner
	2.	define the crease using a nude eyeshadow
	3.	soften it further with a skin-tone shadow
	4.	add depth by contouring with a deeper shade
	5.	pop some shimmer on the lid
	6.	top it off with glitter for that extra glam
	7.	finish with a soft touch on the lower lash line

If you dream of becoming a standout makeup artist, start with these 10 simple yet powerful habits!

1.	Master the Basics – Learn skin prep, foundation matching, and blending techniques.

2.	Practice Daily – The more you practice, the better you get.

3.	Understand Face Shapes – Customize looks for each unique face.

4.	Keep Learning – Stay updated with trends and new products.

5.	Build a Kit Wisely – Invest in quality, versatile products and tools.

6.	Focus on Hygiene – Clean brushes and sanitized products are a must.

7.	Develop Your Signature Style – Stand out with a unique touch or technique.

8.	Work on Different Skin Tones & Types – Gain experience with diverse clients.

9.	Be Patient and Calm – Especially during high-pressure situations like weddings.

10.	Build a Portfolio – Showcase your best work on social media and a website
